1
00:00:36,399 --> 00:00:37,079
Sis

2
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:39,640
I was passing by and came to see you

3
00:00:41,679 --> 00:00:43,320
Why is Bao'er crying?

4
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:44,520
Here, let me hold him

5
00:00:48,079 --> 00:00:48,920
Yingrong

6
00:00:50,399 --> 00:00:51,159
I'm coming

7
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,719
Don't cry, don't cry

8
00:01:04,719 --> 00:01:05,560
There, there

9
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:06,239
What's going on?

10
00:01:06,719 --> 00:01:07,599
Why is he crying?

11
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:08,400
Sis

12
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:09,560
That child

13
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,680
That isn't Bao'er

14
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:12,920
That's a boy from someone else's family

15
00:01:16,719 --> 00:01:17,359
What?

16
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,719
They brought a boy home from outside

17
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:21,480
And they treasure him so much

18
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:23,920
They don't like girls

19
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,120
No

20
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:25,879
Even if he doesn't like girls

21
00:01:25,879 --> 00:01:27,480
he can't just bring a boy home

22
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:29,519
Isn't that stabbing you right in the heart?

23
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,680
That child

24
00:01:35,159 --> 00:01:36,439
what is actually going on?

25
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,359
Did he cheat?

26
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,400
Is it his with someone else?

27
00:01:51,879 --> 00:01:53,159
I'll kill him

28
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,239
He says

29
00:01:58,359 --> 00:02:00,799
it's a boy adopted from another family

30
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:03,840
Do you just believe whatever he says?

31
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:07,200
What else can be done now?

32
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:09,400
The child has already been brought back

33
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,080
At least he's young

34
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,439
and doesn't know anything

35
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,080
Maybe

36
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:16,479
when he grows up

37
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:18,439
he'll truly become our own

38
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:19,560
Listen

39
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:20,360
take him to Wang Yingzhu

40
00:02:20,439 --> 00:02:21,360
and let her feed him

41
00:02:21,759 --> 00:02:22,000
Okay

42
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:22,439
Right away

43
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:28,319
Be careful

44
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,120
My dear grandson

45
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:29,919
Sis

46
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,120
Some things can be tolerated

47
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,080
but some things cannot

48
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:35,599
Mom and I can't soothe him

49
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:36,719
He might be hungry

50
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:37,280
Here

51
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,039
you feed him

52
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:50,879
What are you doing?

53
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,280
My sister and Bao'er need to rest.

54
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,199
Don't let someone else's kid disturb them.

55
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:56,159
The baby Guangming brought back...

56
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,879
That is the Li family's baby.

57
00:02:58,039 --> 00:02:59,560
That is also your sister's baby.

58
00:02:59,639 --> 00:03:01,080
If she doesn't take care of it, who will?

59
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,560
She needs to breastfeed the baby.

60
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:03,800
You went out

61
00:03:03,919 --> 00:03:05,439
and had a baby with god knows who.

62
00:03:05,439 --> 00:03:06,639
You bring it back for my sister to raise?

63
00:03:06,639 --> 00:03:07,759
And even breastfeed him?

64
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:09,280
How can you bully someone like this?

65
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,599
More children, more blessings.

66
00:03:10,599 --> 00:03:12,120
Screw your "more children, more blessings."

67
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,400
My sister has Bao'er.

68
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,199
Having her is enough.

69
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:16,439
I'm doing this for your sister's own good.

70
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,439
Giving birth to a girl...

71
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,879
what use is that?

72
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:20,919
Having a boy to rely on...

73
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,599
she should be thanking me.

74
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:26,400
You're just trying to bully us, aren't you?

75
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:28,000
Li Guangming!

76
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,800
You are not a man.

77
00:03:30,319 --> 00:03:31,240
Don't make a scene.

78
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,919
What mother

79
00:03:33,039 --> 00:03:33,919
doesn't suffer a little?

80
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:35,800
Don't think my sister has no family to back her.

81
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:37,199
If you bully our Wang family,

82
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:38,240
it won't end well for you.

83
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,719
Well, thank you very much.

84
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,759
I have a son now.

85
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:43,560
And I've become a director at the factory.

86
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,840
It's a double blessing for me.

87
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,960
But look at you.

88
00:03:46,479 --> 00:03:47,879
You left the factory,

89
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:49,240
lost your job,

90
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,639
and can't even take care of yourself.

91
00:03:50,639 --> 00:03:51,800
Yet you curse others.

92
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,599
If you ask me,

93
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:53,719
you'll never find anyone

94
00:03:53,719 --> 00:03:55,120
doing worse than you are.

95
00:03:55,599 --> 00:03:56,639
Go ahead and gloat.

96
00:03:56,919 --> 00:03:58,680
Let's see if you have a good ending.

97
00:03:58,919 --> 00:04:00,080
Then just you watch.

98
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:01,759
I have a bright future.

99
00:04:01,759 --> 00:04:03,000
I'm like a rising sun.

100
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:05,240
Your Wang family will be kneeling to beg me.

101
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,120
You think I'm scared of you?

102
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,840
Mom, let's go.

103
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:09,159
You won't just fear us.

104
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:09,960
In the future,

105
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:10,719
you will be the ones kneeling

106
00:04:10,719 --> 00:04:12,199
and begging our Wang family.

107
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,439
Sis.

108
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,519
Don't stay here and take this abuse.

109
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:20,000
Let's go.

110
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:20,800
Come back with me.

111
00:04:22,199 --> 00:04:22,920
Yingrong.

112
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,600
You go back first.

113
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,000
Sis.

114
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:38,000
Listen to me.

115
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,879
I know what I'm doing.

116
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:45,079
That pig at your house...

117
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,519
if you don't take it away today,

118
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,800
I'm going to slaughter it.

119
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,120
Do you hear me?

120
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,720
Are you playing dumb?

121
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,720
Playing crazy?

122
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:52,639
Playing deaf?

123
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,519
I'm going to let the pig out.

124
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,240
Let's see what you can do then.

125
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:05,839
How do you open this?

126
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,360
How do you open this?

127
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,439
What's going on?

128
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,519
Why won't it open?

129
00:05:22,199 --> 00:05:22,759
It got away!

130
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,399
It got away! Run!

131
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,439
Run, pig, run!

132
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,240
Run!

133
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:26,639
Mom!

134
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:27,160
Run!

135
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:28,360
How did the pig get away?

136
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,160
We have to chase it back!

137
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:29,759
I twisted my ankle.

138
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:30,480
I can't chase it.

139
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:44,399
Who said you could touch that car?

140
00:05:44,839 --> 00:05:45,480
Give it back.

141
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,319
Pig.

142
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,240
It's raining!

143
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,439
Time to bring in the laundry!

144
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:51,920
Auntie.

145
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,920
Let me borrow your raincoat.

146
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:53,759
Sure, sure.

147
00:05:53,759 --> 00:05:54,240
Get on.

148
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:56,639
Let's go, hurry up.

149
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,560
My brand new car.

150
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,800
Haven't even warmed it up yet.

151
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:01,839
Here piggy, piggy.

152
00:06:01,839 --> 00:06:02,800
Stop your nagging.

153
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:04,199
Get ready to get off and catch them.

154
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,079
Quick, quick, quick.

155
00:06:07,519 --> 00:06:08,480
You grab a bag.

156
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,079
Okay.

157
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,240
Over there, over there.

158
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:11,720
Catch that one first.

159
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,279
Don't run, don't run.

160
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:14,759
Here piggy, piggy.

161
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,480
Don't run.

162
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,480
Catch it.

163
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:23,920
Over there.

164
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,639
One each.

165
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,480
Don't run.

166
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,920
Didn't know you could catch pigs.

167
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,519
Don't run.

168
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,920
I never thought I'd catch pigs either.

169
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,199
I can actually do it.

170
00:06:45,439 --> 00:06:47,040
Your mom let this pig loose.

171
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:48,519
And now you've caught it.

172
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,439
Making amends.

173
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,920
So I won't be thanking you.

174
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,439
Do you plan to walk back?

175
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:05,800
I'll give you a ride.

176
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,920
Let's get this straight first.

177
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,480
I'm not going to thank you.

178
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,079
Fine, fine, fine.

179
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,360
It's my family that owes you.

180
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,680
Get on.

181
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:22,759
Are you seated?

182
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:28,360
I'll take you part of the way.

183
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,680
I have things to do later.

184
00:07:33,279 --> 00:07:34,920
Be good, piggy.

185
00:07:37,959 --> 00:07:39,920
Stop squealing.

186
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,160
That pig...

187
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:43,279
You actually found it?

188
00:07:43,439 --> 00:07:44,439
Auntie Chen.

189
00:07:44,439 --> 00:07:46,360
You should be glad I found the pig.

190
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,959
Otherwise...

191
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,879
You'd have to compensate me.

192
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:53,120
This pig...

193
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:54,279
Good that it's back.

194
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,319
Good that it's back.

195
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,480
Mom.

196
00:07:56,639 --> 00:07:58,000
My youngest is back.

197
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,040
Not the pig.

198
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:04,920
You just watch your mom get bullied by them?

199
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,920
Bullied by their pig?

200
00:08:07,079 --> 00:08:07,759
Mom.

201
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,439
What can I do?

202
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:11,839
Slaughter it for me!

203
00:08:13,759 --> 00:08:16,360
I mean, go slaughter that pig.

204
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,720
Anyway, I can't accept

205
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,920
raising pigs in this courtyard.

206
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:19,720
Mom.

207
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:21,279
You want me

208
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,319
to slaughter Wang Yingrong's pig?

209
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:24,360
Is there a problem?

210
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,639
Then the next step

211
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,639
would be her slaughtering me.

212
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:31,800
You...

213
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,879
Are you a man or not?

214
00:08:33,879 --> 00:08:35,279
What's the use of raising you?

215
00:08:36,279 --> 00:08:37,240
Sister Yingrong, I was wrong!

216
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,360
Don't hit me!

217
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:42,039
Zheng Xiaochuan, you dare pull a girl's pigtails?

218
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,360
Will you do it again?

219
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,480
I know I was wrong, Sister Yingrong.

220
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,200
Will you do it again?

221
00:08:45,759 --> 00:08:48,159
Will you dare pull a girl's pigtails again?

222
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,559
Why are you just standing there?

223
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,000
Say something!

224
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,320
Are you going or not?

225
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:56,080
Mom.

226
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:58,279
I am absolutely and positively certain...

227
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,159
I...

228
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,519
I can't beat her.

229
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,799
They say raise sons for security in old age.

230
00:09:04,799 --> 00:09:06,080
Tell me, I gave birth to you three...

231
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,200
...what use are you?

232
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:10,600
It smells like pig manure everywhere.

233
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,480
Look who it is

234
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,960
The Zheng family's second son has been released from prison

235
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,039
Let's go, let's go

236
00:09:42,879 --> 00:09:43,879
Mom

237
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,759
Anyway, there's still Big Brother and Second Brother

238
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,559
So don't count on me

239
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:49,000
Expect a little less from me

240
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,480
and you'll be a little less disappointed

241
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,399
You, you, you...

242
00:09:51,519 --> 00:09:53,159
Are you trying to drive me to my grave?

243
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,120
Thanks, Mom

244
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,360
Third Brother

245
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:00,639
Second Brother

246
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,360
Mom

247
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,159
Mom

248
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,440
Second Brother is back

249
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,200
Mom

250
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:11,200
Number Two

251
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,279
Number Two

252
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,320
My Number Two is back

253
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:18,759
Mom missed you to death

254
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,840
You're darker

255
00:10:24,039 --> 00:10:25,159
You're thinner

256
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:29,879
Big Brother

257
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,039
Where have you been these past few months?

258
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:33,879
I went to the prison to pick you up

259
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,879
but the officers said you'd already left

260
00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:38,720
You've been out for so long

261
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:40,559
didn't you know to send word home?

262
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:43,000
I finally found out where you were

263
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:45,799
and rushed to pick you up

264
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:47,559
but you came back on your own

265
00:10:48,519 --> 00:10:49,440
I found a place

266
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:50,879
and did some odd jobs

267
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,600
I couldn't come back empty-handed

268
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:54,679
Second Brother

269
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,039
It's good that you're back safe

270
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,360
Welcome home, Second Brother

271
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:00,279
Number Two

272
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,840
All these years you weren't home

273
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:04,639
Mom was bullied terribly by others

274
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:05,080
Mom

275
00:11:06,039 --> 00:11:07,080
What do you want me to do?

276
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:07,840
Just say it

277
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,360
Go take that pig from the Wang family

278
00:11:10,919 --> 00:11:11,960
and slaughter it

279
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:14,919
Mom

280
00:11:20,559 --> 00:11:21,200
Second Brother

281
00:11:24,879 --> 00:11:25,759
What are you thinking?

282
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:27,679
You just got out and you want to go back in?

283
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,159
Or do you want Second Brother to go back in, Mom?

284
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,720
I owe Mom too much for all these years

285
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,120
Whatever Mom wants me to do

286
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,639
I will do it

287
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:39,879
How about

288
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,559
we eat first?

289
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,000
Number Two, all these years

290
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,279
surely hasn't had anything good to eat

291
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,840
I... I'll go make food

292
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,360
I'll go make something tasty

293
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,320
Watch your words and actions from now on

